    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thank you, I can confirm the issue is solved:\r\n\r\nHeads-up for future: \r\n\r\nI have created a custom ACL with `search` and `browse` features only, and injected a custom client to instantsearch, just like this:\r\n\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// custom client\r\nvar customClient = algoliasearch('appid', 'search_and_browse_only_custom_acl_key');\r\n// Create instant_search index and set its settings\r\nvar customIndex = customClient.initIndex('my_index');\r\ncustomIndex.setSettings({\r\n  paginationLimitedTo: 10000\r\n});\r\n// / custom client\r\n\r\nvar search = instantsearch({\r\n  appId: 'appid',\r\n  apiKey: 'search_and_browse_only_custom_acl_key',\r\n  indexName: '',\r\n  createAlgoliaClient: function(algoliasearch, appId, apiKey) { \r\n    return customClient;\r\n   }\r\n  // my other custom settings / preferences for search...\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n**But, as suggested and mentioned in most places, try avoiding this if this is really not a must. This decreases overall performance of your search, also allows crawlers to scrape your site**",
    "created_at": "2017-04-20T15:10:51Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2118#issuecomment-295772304",
